Solar Millennium Near Finance Agreement on $3.8 Billion California Plant

-- B y   M a r c   R o c a
-- 
2011-03-03T12:56:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/solar-millennium-near-finance-deal-on-3-8-billion-u-s-plant.html
  Solar Millennium AG (S2M)  is close to an
agreement to finance its $3.8 billion solar thermal project in  California  and said it has projects with a capacity to produce a
total of 2.7 gigawatts of electricity under planning.  Chief Executive Officer Christoph Wolff said the financing
may be finished in the summer. It is expected to include funds
from the U.S. Department of Energy.  In an interview, Wolff said about 300 megawatts of the
projects the company is planning are outside the U.S. and Spain.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marc Roca in London at 
 mroca6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  